<div id="review_668379627" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/668379627" />
    <a title="Elizabeth (Alaska)" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2026178-elizabeth-alaska"><img alt="Elizabeth (Alaska)" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1304966095p2/2026178.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/668379627?book_show_action=true">Jul 26, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Elizabeth (Alaska)" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Elizabeth (Alaska)" href="/user/show/2026178-elizabeth-alaska">Elizabeth (Alaska)</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title=" " href="/book/show/18302742-the-sound-of-the-mountain">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2026178-elizabeth-alaska?shelf=gr-recommended">gr-recommended</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2026178-elizabeth-alaska?shelf=mid-20th-century">mid-20th-century</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2026178-elizabeth-alaska?shelf=asia">asia</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2026178-elizabeth-alaska?shelf=kindle">kindle</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer668379627" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15388897114043841926">I don&apos;t know where to begin. This is almost devoid of plot. Well, there is really is no &apos;almost&apos; to it. I should say clearly that there is no plot. It&apos;s not as if absolutely nothing happens, it&apos;s just that it is the day to day things that happen. Still, in a couple of places those day to day things are not the things encountered in most lives, particularly not in western lives. <br/><br/>Normally I would complain about the simplicity of the prose. However, it was exactly right - pitch perfect, in fact - s</span>
  <span id="freeText15388897114043841926" style="display:none">I don't know where to begin. This is almost devoid of plot. Well, there is really is no 'almost' to it. I should say clearly that there is no plot. It's not as if absolutely nothing happens, it's just that it is the day to day things that happen. Still, in a couple of places those day to day things are not the things encountered in most lives, particularly not in western lives. <br /><br />Normally I would complain about the simplicity of the prose. However, it was exactly right - pitch perfect, in fact - so that there was no question this was a Japanese novel. I say that in case the Japanese names didn't make it obvious. Still, there was something in the very cadence of the language that made it clearer, that helped to bring the culture itself to the fore.<br /><br />Given the GR description, and the novel's opening lines, I expected this to be predominantly about an aging man, Ogata Shingo. He notices his age a few times, and there is one scene in particular where age is an issue. Should the age factor and memory problem have continued, this would still have been a very good novel. It was so much more than that. Perhaps what struck me almost thunderously, was that this older man in post-war Japan, should be concerned about women's issues.<br /><br />I chose to read this at this time because of a GR group that will be discussing it. I very much look forward to that discussion in lieu of making more remarks here. This sits on the line between 4- and 5-stars. I would like it to spill over to the higher number, but I can't quite make myself tick that box.</span>
  <a data-text-id="15388897114043841926" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


