<span id="freeTextContainer1443923455420722173">Japanese literature tends to be a little hit and miss for me, and I was not pulled in at all by Kawabata&apos;s <i>The Sound of the Mountain</i>. The first section was rather dull, and I also found the translation too flat and matter-of-fact to suit my personal reading tastes.</span>
  <span id="freeText1443923455420722173" style="display:none">Japanese literature tends to be a little hit and miss for me, and I was not pulled in at all by Kawabata's <i>The Sound of the Mountain</i>. The first section was rather dull, and I also found the translation too flat and matter-of-fact to suit my personal reading tastes.</span>
